# Next.js basics

Use **[Next.js documentation](https://nextjs.org/docs/)** as the framework source of truth. This repo is **Payload-led** for CMS schema, access, and migrations — see **`payload-basics.mdc`** for boundaries and **`getPayload`** usage. These rules add **Next.js App Router** depth and route agents to **`next-*.mdc`** topic files via **`next-features-overview.mdc`**.

## What is Next.js?

From the [docs home](https://nextjs.org/docs/): Next.js is a **React framework** for full-stack apps — UI with React components, plus routing, data conventions, and optimizations. Lower-level bundlers/compilers are configured so product work stays in **`src/app`**, Route Handlers, and **`next.config.js`**.

## How the docs are organized

Official structure ([How to use the docs](https://nextjs.org/docs/)):

| Section | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| **Getting Started** | Step-by-step path to a new app and core features |
| **Guides** | Topic tutorials — pick what you need |
| **API Reference** | Technical reference per feature |

Navigate by sidebar or search (**⌘K** / **Ctrl+K**). Full **docs** index: **[`/docs/llms.txt`](https://nextjs.org/docs/llms.txt)** (preferred for agents — docs-shaped tree). **Site-wide URLs:** [nextjs.org/sitemap.xml](https://nextjs.org/sitemap.xml) enumerates the whole marketing site (blog, showcase, conf, **and** docs paths); use when you need every crawlable `loc`, bearing in mind it is large and mixed-scope versus **`llms.txt`**. Many pages expose **Markdown** via **`.md`** on the URL (e.g. [`/docs/app/getting-started.md`](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/getting-started.md)).

## App Router vs Pages Router

Next ships **two routers** ([docs](https://nextjs.org/docs/)):

| Router | Notes |
|--------|--------|
| **App Router** | Under `app/` — Server Components, streaming, current features — **[Using App Router](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/getting-started)** |
| **Pages Router** | Legacy `pages/` — still supported — **[Pages Router docs](https://nextjs.org/docs/pages)** |

Use the **sidebar dropdown** on [nextjs.org/docs](https://nextjs.org/docs/) to switch doc sets. **This repo’s delivery layer targets the App Router** (`src/app`).

### React version handling (official behavior)

- **App Router:** Uses the **React canary** bundled with Next (stable React 19 behavior + framework-validated features).
- **Pages Router:** Uses **`react` / `react-dom` from your `package.json`**.

